RISC-V 64-bit UEFI hex source generators
========================================

These Python scripts generate the hand-coded machine code (hex0 / hex1 / hex2
format) for the riscv64 UEFI bootstrap tools. Each script embeds a RISC-V
instruction encoder (see rv64enc.py) and builds the binary with a Builder class
that resolves labels automatically.

Generators and the artifacts they produce
------------------------------------------
  gen-hex1-rv64.py          -> ../../riscv64/hex1.hex0  (hex1 compiler, Phase 1)
  gen-hex2-rv64.py          -> ../../riscv64/hex2.hex1  (hex2 linker, Phase 2)
  gen-M0-rv64.py            -> ../../riscv64/M0.hex2     (M0 macro assembler)
  gen-catm-rv64.py          -> ../../riscv64/catm.hex2   (catm concatenator)
  gen-kaem-optional-rv64.py -> (reference only -- see "Hand-maintained" below)

Each script writes the hex source to stdout, e.g.:

  python3 gen-hex1-rv64.py > ../../riscv64/hex1.hex0

The committed artifacts carry richer hand-written documentation comments than
the generators emit, so the two are NOT byte-identical -- but their machine
content (hex bytes plus hex2 label/ref directives, with comments and whitespace
ignored) must match. verify-gen.sh enforces exactly that and is wired into the
top-level Makefile as `make verify-riscv64-gen`. Run it after editing any
generator; when you change machine code, re-run the generator into its artifact.

Hand-maintained artifacts (NOT generated)
-----------------------------------------
  ../../riscv64/hex0.hex0           No generator exists; this is the root hex0
                                    seed and is maintained by hand.
  ../../riscv64/kaem-optional.hex0  Hand-tuned after generation. Its generator
                                    (gen-kaem-optional-rv64.py) is a historical
                                    reference that has since diverged and does
                                    NOT reproduce the committed binary; the
                                    committed file is authoritative. verify-gen.sh
                                    deliberately does not check these two.

Helpers
-------
  rv64enc.py        RISC-V instruction encoder (R/I/S/B/U/J forms), cross-checked
                    against GNU as.
  hex2_helper.py, hex2_sim.py, kaem_helper.py, assemble_hex2.py
                    Supporting library / simulator / assembly utilities used by
                    the generators and during development.
